# [<tag>] (When applying this commit, it will...) <subject> (Maximum 72 characters)
# |<----   Preferably up to 50 characters   --->|<------------------->|
# Example:
# [feat] Introduction of automated commit messages

# (Optional) Explain why this change was made
# |<----   Try to limit each line to a maximum of 72 characters  ---->|

# (Optional) Provide links or identifiers for relevant tickets, tasks, or other resources
# Example: Github issue #23

# --- COMMIT END ---
# The tag can be
#    feat     (new functionality)
#    fix      (bug fix)
#    refactor (code refactoring)
#    style    (formatting, missing indents, etc.; no production code changes)
#    doc      (documentation updates)
#    test     (adding or refactoring tests; no production code changes)
#    version  (version bump/release; no production code changes)
#    license  (licensing changes; no production code changes)
#    hack     (temporary solution; please avoid it)
#    defaults (default value changes)

# --------------------
# Remember:
#   * The subject line should start with a capital letter.
#   * Do not end the subject line with a period.
#   * Separate the subject line from the body description with a blank line.
#   * Use the description to explain what, why, and how.
#   * You can create lists using "-" or "*" at the start of each line in the description.
# --------------------
